Seeding is providing bandwidth for people to download from what you've already downloaded from a file. That's why torrents are so popular, it's like sharing pages from a book until you have the whole thing as opposed to waiting for the next piece in line, thus making it quick. 

And for those of you who say "seed! seed" You're wrong 99% of the time, I downloaded this at 1.5 MB a second, it took me less than 3  hours for the entire thing. And it works VERY good in pcsx! Works better than almost any of the other files I've tried. Thank you very, very much for this. Too broke to go out and get a PS2, even.
